Hi @georgios,

Let's be backward compatible and keep the setHttpClient. It could be that customers want to use their own Client. we can do something like:
```
public ClientInterface createHttpClient() {
    if(this.httpClient != null) {
        try {
            return this.httpClient.getClass().newInstance();
        } catch (InstantiationException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        } catch (IllegalAccessException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
    return new HttpURLConnectionClient();
}

public void setHttpClient(ClientInterface httpClient) {
    this.httpClient = httpClient;
}
```
